---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Benson Hendrix — Web Designer & Digital Media Strategist">

<section class="px-8 pt-24 pb-8 max-w-6xl mx-auto">

  <p class="text-sm font-sans uppercase tracking-widest text-muted mb-8">
    Web Designer & Digital Media Strategist
  </p>

  <h1 class="font-display font-black text-ink leading-none mb-10" 
      style="font-size: clamp(4rem, 10vw, 9rem); font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144, 'WONK' 1;">
    Designing for<br />
    <em class="text-accent">impact.</em><br />
    Not templates.
  </h1>

  <div class="border-l-4 border-accent pl-8 mb-12 max-w-2xl">
    <p class="text-xl text-muted leading-relaxed font-sans">
      I build digital experiences for higher education — from emergency migrations to full redesigns. Strategy first, design always.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="flex gap-6">
    <a href="#work" class="bg-ink text-paper px-8 py-4 font-sans text-sm font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-accent transition-colors">
      View My Work
    </a>
    <a href="#contact" class="border border-ink text-ink px-8 py-4 font-sans text-sm font-semibold no-underline hover:border-accent hover:text-accent transition-colors">
      Get In Touch
    </a>
  </div>

</section>
  <section id="work" class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-8 py-24">

  <div class="flex items-baseline gap-6 mb-16 pb-8 border-b border-ink/10">
    <span class="font-display text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-muted">Selected Work</span>
  </div>

  <div class="flex flex-col divide-y divide-ink/10">

    <!-- Case Study 01 -->
    <div class="py-16">
      <div class="flex gap-8 items-start">
        <span class="font-display text-8xl font-black leading-none select-none" style="color: #1C191708;">01</span>
        <div class="flex-1">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-4 flex-wrap gap-4">
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-muted font-sans">NMHU · 2022–Present · In Progress</span>
            <a href="/work/nmhu-redesign" class="text-sm font-sans text-accent no-underline hover:underline">View Case Study →</a>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold text-ink mb-4 leading-tight">
            Redesigning a University's<br />Digital Front Door
          </h3>
          <p class="text-muted max-w-2xl mb-6 leading-relaxed font-sans">
            Eight months into a multi-year overhaul of NMHU's primary web presence. Introduced audience and decision-based navigation, restructured a nearly flat URL architecture, built a searchable Program Finder, and integrated SearchStax site search and ReciteMe accessibility tools — all on WordPress with Divi.
          </p>
          <div class="flex gap-2 flex-wrap">
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-muted px-3 py-1">WordPress</span>
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-muted px-3 py-1">Divi</span>
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-muted px-3 py-1">Information Architecture</span>
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-muted px-3 py-1">UX</span>
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-muted px-3 py-1">Accessibility</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Case Study 02 -->
    <div class="py-16">
      <div class="flex gap-8 items-start">
        <span class="font-display text-8xl font-black leading-none select-none" style="color: #1C191708;">02</span>
        <div class="flex-1">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-4 flex-wrap gap-4">
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-muted font-sans">New Mexico Tech · 2018</span>
            <a href="/work/nmt-redesign" class="text-sm font-sans text-accent no-underline hover:underline">View Case Study →</a>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold text-ink mb-4 leading-tight">
            Cutting Content Migration<br />Time in Half
          </h3>
          <p class="text-muted max-w-2xl mb-6 leading-relaxed font-sans">
            Joined New Mexico Tech's redesign mid-project and drove the launch of a new OmniCMS site. Through intensive project management and workflow optimization, reduced content migration from 10 weeks to 5 — completing the equivalent of a full semester's work in half the time.
          </p>
          <div class="flex gap-2 flex-wrap">
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-muted px-3 py-1">OmniCMS</span>
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-muted px-3 py-1">Project Management</span>
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-muted px-3 py-1">Content Strategy</span>
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-muted px-3 py-1">CMS Migration</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Case Study 03 -->
    <div class="py-16">
      <div class="flex gap-8 items-start">
        <span class="font-display text-8xl font-black leading-none select-none" style="color: #1C191708;">03</span>
        <div class="flex-1">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-4 flex-wrap gap-4">
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-muted font-sans">NMHU · 2024</span>
            <a href="/work/nmhu-migration" class="text-sm font-sans text-accent no-underline hover:underline">View Case Study →</a>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold text-ink mb-4 leading-tight">
            A PHP Crisis Averted
          </h3>
          <p class="text-muted max-w-2xl mb-6 leading-relaxed font-sans">
            When a PHP 8.2 upgrade threatened to take NMHU's existing site offline, designed and executed an emergency migration to a new WordPress template — keeping the institution's digital presence live without interruption while laying the groundwork for the full redesign that followed.
          </p>
          <div class="flex gap-2 flex-wrap">
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-muted px-3 py-1">WordPress</span>
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-muted px-3 py-1">PHP</span>
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-muted px-3 py-1">Crisis Management</span>
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-muted px-3 py-1">CMS Migration</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Case Study 04 -->
    <div class="py-16">
      <div class="flex gap-8 items-start">
        <span class="font-display text-8xl font-black leading-none select-none" style="color: #1C191708;">04</span>
        <div class="flex-1">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-4 flex-wrap gap-4">
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-muted font-sans">NMHU · Ongoing</span>
            <a href="/work/social-media" class="text-sm font-sans text-accent no-underline hover:underline">View Case Study →</a>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold text-ink mb-4 leading-tight">
            Building Consistent<br />Brand Presence
          </h3>
          <p class="text-muted max-w-2xl mb-6 leading-relaxed font-sans">
            Event coverage for Homecoming, Graduation, and major institutional moments across Instagram and Facebook — developing a consistent visual language for NMHU's social channels and building audience engagement through intentional image curation and storytelling.
          </p>
          <div class="flex gap-2 flex-wrap">
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-muted px-3 py-1">Social Media</span>
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-muted px-3 py-1">Visual Design</span>
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-muted px-3 py-1">Brand</span>
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-muted px-3 py-1">Event Coverage</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<section id="about" class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-8 py-24">
  
   <div class="flex items-baseline gap-6 mb-16 pb-8 border-b border-ink/10">
    <span class="font-display text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-muted">About</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-16">
    
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-6">
      <p class="text-xl text-ink leading-relaxed font-sans">It used to be said that 'Athletics programs are the front porch of a university.' But now it's a university's digital presence that's usually the first thing students and their families see. It's my job to make sure that presence is positive, secure, and up to date.</p>
      <p class="text-xl text-ink leading-relaxed font-sans">So I'm responsible for that first impression a student has for New Mexico Highlands. And with that responsibility I decided the website needed more than a fresh coat of paint. It needs to be stripped to the frame and rebuilt like a muscle car. I started working on that new look and feel to the website.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-6">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-display text-ink font-bold border-b border-ink/10 mb-2 pb-4" >Skills & Tools</h3>
      <ul class="list-none flex flex-row flex-wrap gap-2">
        <li class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-gray-700 px-3 py-1">WordPress & Divi</li>
        <li class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-gray-700 px-3 py-1">Astro</li>
        <li class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-gray-700 px-3 py-1">HTML / CSS / Tailwind</li>
        <li class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-gray-700 px-3 py-1">Information Architecture</li>
        <li class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-gray-700 px-3 py-1">Digital Accessibility</li>
        <li class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-gray-700 px-3 py-1">Social Media Strategy</li>
        <li class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-gray-700 px-3 py-1">SearchStax</li>
        <li class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-gray-700 px-3 py-1">ReciteMe</li>
        <li class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider border border-ink/20 text-gray-700 px-3 py-1">AI-Assisted Content Workflows</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

  </div>

</section>

<section id="contact" class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-8 py-24">

   <div class="flex items-baseline gap-6 mb-16 pb-8 border-b border-ink/10">
    <span class="font-display text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-muted">Contact Me</span>
  </div>

  <h2 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold text-ink mb-6 leading-tight">
  Let's work together.
  </h2>

    <p class="text-xl text-ink leading-relaxed font-sans max-w-2xl">From content strategy to information architecture, web design to social media, if you're interested in working together, or if your institution needs a fresh set of eyes to look it over, I'm always happy to help. If you need a conference speaker or workshop leader, please feel free to reach out to me.</p>

  <div class="flex gap-6 pt-4">
    <a href="mailto:benson@bensonhendrix.com" class="bg-ink text-paper px-8 py-4 font-sans text-sm font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-accent transition-colors">
      Email Me
    </a>
    <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/bensonhendrix" class="border border-accent text-ink px-8 py-4 font-sans text-sm font-semibold no-underline hover:border-accent hover:text-accent transition-colors">
      Find Me On LinkedIn
    </a>
  </div>
</section>


</Layout>